UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 152
1 AN ACT relating to nationally certified student support personnel.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 157 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 Notwithstanding any other statute to the contrary:
6 (1) (a) If funds are appropriated by the General Assembly for this purpose, a local
7 board of education shall provide an annual salary supplement to all school
8 social workers:
9 1. Who are employed as a certified employee by the local board of
10 education to provide or coordinate counseling or social work services
11 for students in a public school setting; and
12 2. Who hold an active national certification as a school social worker
13 from the School Social Work Association of America.
14 (b) The salary supplement shall be in the same amount as the salary
15 supplement provided to a public school teacher who has attained
16 certification from the National Board for Professional Teaching Standards
17 as provided in KRS 157.395. If the amount appropriated by the General
18 Assembly is less than the amount necessary to meet the requirements of this
19 paragraph, the salary supplement received by each qualified school social
20 worker shall be reduced proportionately by the Department of Education so
21 that all eligible individuals receive the same amount as a supplement.
22 (c) The supplement shall remain available to a school social worker so long as
23 funds are appropriated for this purpose by the General Assembly and the
24 school social worker continues to meet the requirements established by this
25 subsection. The supplement shall cease if the school social worker is
26 employed in another capacity by the local board where the provision of
27 school social work services is incidental to his or her other duties.
