UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 152
1 (d) The Department of Education shall:
2 1. Determine how many school social workers qualify for the supplement
3 each year;
4 2. Determine the amount of the supplement available each year for each
5 qualified school social worker based on appropriated funds available;
6 3. Notify each local board of education of the supplement amount
7 available to each qualifying school social worker employed by the
8 local board of education; and
9 4. Develop a process for payment to local boards of education of
10 supplement amounts due;
11 (2) If funds are not appropriated by the General Assembly to support the salary
12 supplement established by subsection (1) of this section, a local board of
13 education may provide an annual salary supplement under the conditions
14 established by subsection (1) of this section using the resources available to the
15 local board of education; and
16 (3) The supplement authorized by this section shall be considered in the calculation
17 for contributions to the Teachers' Retirement System.
18 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 157 IS CREATED TO
19 READ AS FOLLOWS:
20 Notwithstanding any other statute to the contrary:
21 (1) (a) If funds are appropriated by the General Assembly for this purpose, a local
22 board of education shall provide an annual salary supplement to all school
23 psychologists:
24 1. Who are employed as a certified employee by the local board of
25 education to provide or coordinate school psychologist services for
26 students in a public school setting; and
27 2. Who hold an active nationally certified school psychologist credential
