1 from the National Association of School Psychologists.
2 (b) The salary supplement shall be in the same amount as the salary
3 supplement provided to a public school teacher who has attained
4 certification from the National Board for Professional Teaching Standards
5 as provided in KRS 157.395. If the amount appropriated by the General
6 Assembly is less than the amount necessary to meet the requirements of this
7 paragraph, the salary supplement received by each qualified school
8 psychologist shall be reduced proportionately by the Department of
9 Education so that all eligible individuals receive the same amount as a
10 supplement.
11 (c) The supplement shall remain available to a school psychologist so long as
12 funds are appropriated for this purpose by the General Assembly and the
13 school psychologist continues to meet the requirements established by this
14 subsection. The supplement shall cease if the school psychologist is
15 employed in another capacity by the local board where the provision of
16 school psychologist services is incidental to his or her other duties.
17 (d) The Department of Education shall:
18 1. Determine how many school psychologists qualify for the supplement
19 each year;
20 2. Determine the amount of the supplement available each year for each
21 qualified school psychologist based on appropriated funds available;
22 3. Notify each local board of education of the supplement amount
23 available to each qualifying school psychologist employed by the local
24 board of education; and
25 4. Develop a process for payment to local boards of education of
26 supplement amounts due;
27 (2) If funds are not appropriated by the General Assembly to support the salary
